\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 11. A. vestita} Willk. in Willk. & Lange, {\i Prodr. Fl. Hisp.}{\b  2:} 366 (1868). Herb; stock somewhat lax with few branches. Leaves acuminate, subacute, muticous, with narrow scarious margins, velutinous, erect, dimorphic; outer 50-70 × 4-7 mm, lanceolate; inner 80-100 × 1·5-3 mm, linear-spathulate. Scapes 37-45 cm, stout, puberulent mainly at base. Sheath 35-45 mm. Capitula c. 17 mm wide; involucral bracts velutinous; outer longer than the inner, acuminate, long-cuspidate-spinescent, with very narrow scarious margins; inner mucronate to muticous, with wide scarious margins. Spikelets subsessile; bract nearly as long as calyx, velutinous. Calyx 6·5-7 mm; tube hirsute on ribs; awns 1-1·3 mm. Corolla pink.{\i  Mountain pastures. • W.C. Spain}. Hs.
